comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T10:58:03.028Z",codex,"PR #21 finishing verification (2026-07-10): fixed Greptile/Cubic/Gemini findings by preserving exact JSONL multi-state statuses through import/upsert; applying sync --filter consistently to import and export; separating import --status/--type semantics from export filtering; writing empty re-exports for convergence; sanitizing JSONL kv values; correcting --no-section-tags and --reverse docs; simplifying sync returns; and registering the full SDK importer command contract so positional files/new flags actually reach the handler. Functional checks in fresh /tmp/fx-pm-todos-clean: local install activated, timeout 20 pm --help exit 0; JSONL sync --filter status=blocked imported 1 and wrote 1 blocked row while excluding a closed row; sync --status draft wrote all 4 store rows (not an accidental export filter); zero-match sync wrote 0 rows and truncated file to 0 bytes; malformed JSONL exited 1 with structured CommandError-style diagnostics and no stack. Explicit markdown --metadata --priority-map letter --reverse export -> import --upsert -> export normalized diff exit 0; [Task] tag count stayed 1 -> 1. This test first exposed letter priority duplication ((B) -> (B) (B)); fixed parser and added regression test. Default output matched origin/main after timestamp normalization (diff exit 0). Tests 117/117 pass; changelog:full and changelog:check pass. Hound generated dist ES5 warnings are invalid because package targets modern ESM/Node >=22."
